if I didn't say. . .

751
01:03:58,520 --> 01:04:01,640
. . .that you brought some meaning back
into my life.

752
01:04:03,400 --> 01:04:06,040
I am amusing, I suppose.

753
01:04:06,240 --> 01:04:10,840
I have the finest couturier in Vienna
and a glittering circle of friends.

754
01:04:11,040 --> 01:04:14,040
-I do give some rather gay parties.
-Oh, yes.

755
01:04:14,280 --> 01:04:16,040
But take all that away. . .

756
01:04:16,240 --> 01:04:20,440
. . .and you have just wealthy,
unattached little me. . .

757
01:04:21,120 --> 01:04:23,440
. . .searching, just like you.

758
01:04:28,320 --> 01:04:29,960
More strudel, Herr Detweiler?

759
01:04:30,200 --> 01:04:31,680
-How many have I had?
-Two.

760
01:04:31,920 --> 01:04:33,760
Make it an uneven three.

761
01:04:36,920 --> 01:04:39,840
Still eating, Max?
Must be unhappy.

762
01:04:40,040 --> 01:04:43,840
That mixed quartet I've been trying
to steal away from Sol Hurok. . .

763
01:04:44,080 --> 01:04:46,640
-What happened?
-. . .Sascha Petrie stole them first.

764
01:04:46,840 --> 01:04:48,080
I hate thieves.

765
01:04:48,320 --> 01:04:51,480
Max, you really must try
and learn to love yourself.

766
01:04:51,720 --> 01:04:53,960
I had to call Paris, Rome
and Stockholm.

767
01:04:54,200 --> 01:04:57,640
-On Georg's telephone, of course.
-How else could I afford it?

768
01:04:58,080 --> 01:05:03,000
I like rich people, the way they live
and how I live when I'm with them.

769
01:05:03,280 --> 01:05:05,200
I wonder where the children are.

770
01:05:05,600 --> 01:05:08,040
They must have heard
I was coming and hid.

771
01:05:08,280 --> 01:05:10,680
I was hoping they'd be here
to welcome you.

772
01:05:10,920 --> 01:05:15,240
Max, do step out of character for
a moment and try and be charming.

773
01:05:23,920 --> 01:05:25,240
Well?

774
01:05:26,120 --> 01:05:27,280
Well what?

775
01:05:27,480 --> 01:05:30,280
Have you made up his mind?
Do I hear wedding bells?

776
01:05:30,520 --> 01:05:32,440
-Pealing madly.
-Marvelous.

777
01:05:32,680 --> 01:05:35,280
-Not necessarily for me.
-What kind of talk's that?

778
01:05:35,480 --> 01:05:37,040
None-of-your-business talk.

779
01:05:37,280 --> 01:05:39,680
I'm terribly fond of him,
so don't toy with us.

780
01:05:39,920 --> 01:05:43,360
But I'm a child. I like toys.
So tell me everything.

781
01:05:43,600 --> 01:05:48,520
Come on. Tell me every teensy-weensy,
intimate, disgusting detail.

782
01:05:49,920 --> 01:05:53,880
Well, let's just say I have a feeling
I may be here on approval.

783
01:05:54,120 --> 01:05:57,040
-I approve of that. How can you miss?
-Far too easily.

784
01:05:57,280 --> 01:06:00,360
If I know you, darling,
and I do, you will find a way.

785
01:06:00,600 --> 01:06:03,040
-He's no ordinary man.
-No, he's rich.

786
01:06:03,280 --> 01:06:05,440
His wife's death gave him
a great heartache.

787
01:06:05,640 --> 01:06:08,640
And your husband's death
gave you a great fortune.

788
01:06:08,840 --> 01:06:10,720
Oh, Max, you really are a beast.

789
01:06:10,920 --> 01:06:14,800
You and Georg are like family.
That's why I want to see you married.

790
01:06:15,000 --> 01:06:18,440
We must keep all that lovely money
in the family.

791
01:06:34,040 --> 01:06:36,880
-What are you doing there?
-Oh, Captain von Trapp.

792
01:06:37,120 --> 01:06:39,080
I was just looking for. . . .

793
01:06:39,920 --> 01:06:42,640
I didn't see, I mean,
I didn't know you were--

794
01:06:43,200 --> 01:06:44,840
Heil Hitler!

795
01:06:45,520 --> 01:06:46,960
Who are you?

796
01:06:47,200 --> 01:06:49,360
I have a telegram for Herr Detweiler.

797
01:06:49,560 --> 01:06:52,240
-I am Herr Detweiler.
-Yes, sir.

798
01:06:57,080 --> 01:06:59,640
You've delivered your telegram.
Now get out.

799
01:07:06,080 --> 01:07:09,320
-Georg, he's just a boy.
-Yes, and I'm just an Austrian.

800
01:07:09,520 --> 01:07:12,240
Things will happen.
Make sure they don't happen to you.

801
01:07:12,480 --> 01:07:15,080
Max! Don't you ever say that again.

802
01:07:15,320 --> 01:07:17,440
I have no political convictions.

803
01:07:17,680 --> 01:07:20,440
-Can I help it if other people do?
-You can help it.

804
01:07:21,520 --> 01:07:23,640
You must help it.

805
01:07:33,520 --> 01:07:35,040
Hello?

806
01:07:37,520 --> 01:07:40,240
You're far away. Where are you?

807
01:07:40,520 --> 01:07:44,240
In a world that's disappearing,
I'm afraid.

808
01:07:45,040 --> 01:07:48,440
Is there any way I could bring you
back to the world I'm in?

809
01:08:13,320 --> 01:08:15,760
-Father! Father!
-There's your father!

810
01:08:16,480 --> 01:08:19,040
Oh, captain, you're home!

811
01:08:27,080 --> 01:08:29,640
Come out of that water at once!

812
01:08:38,320 --> 01:08:40,440
Oh, you must be Baroness Schraeder.

813
01:08:45,520 --> 01:08:48,440
I'm soaked to the skin!

814
01:08:59,920 --> 01:09:01,240
Straight line!

815
01:09:15,320 --> 01:09:17,640
This is Baroness Schraeder.

816
01:09:20,120 --> 01:09:21,840
And these. . .

817
01:09:22,040 --> 01:09:23,640
. . .are my children.

818
01:09:24,600 --> 01:09:26,080
How do you do?

819
01:09:27,120 --> 01:09:31,640
Go inside, dry off, clean up, change
your clothes and report back here!

820
01:09:36,440 --> 01:09:38,440
Fräulein, you will stay here, please!

821
01:09:40,120 --> 01:09:43,520
I think I'd better go see
what Max is up to.

822
01:09:53,320 --> 01:09:55,040
Now, fräulein. . .

823
01:09:56,880 --> 01:09:58,840
. . .I want a truthful answer.

824
01:09:59,240 --> 01:10:00,640
Yes, captain.

825
01:10:00,920 --> 01:10:04,840
Is it possible,
or could I have just imagined it?

826
01:10:06,280 --> 01:10:10,560
Have my children, by any chance,
been climbing trees today?

827
01:10:11,040 --> 01:10:12,160
Yes, captain.

828
01:10:13,200 --> 01:10:14,440
I see.

829
01:10:15,000 --> 01:10:19,320
And where, may I ask,
did they get these. . . .

830
01:10:19,560 --> 01:10:21,560
-Play clothes.
-Is that what they are?

831
01:10:21,760 --> 01:10:25,040
I made them from the drapes
that used to hang in my bedroom.

832
01:10:25,800 --> 01:10:27,840
-Drapes?
-They have plenty of wear left.

833
01:10:28,040 --> 01:10:29,880
We've been everywhere in them.

834
01:10:30,120 --> 01:10:34,440
Are you telling me that my children
have been roaming about Salzburg. . .

835
01:10:34,640 --> 01:10:37,840
. . .dressed up in nothing
but some old drapes?

836
01:10:38,040 --> 01:10:39,640
And having a marvelous time!

837
01:10:39,840 --> 01:10:42,960
-They have uniforms.
-Forgive me, straitjackets.

838
01:10:43,160 --> 01:10:45,840
They can't be children
if they worry about clothes--

839
01:10:46,080 --> 01:10:47,160
They don't complain.

840
01:10:47,400 --> 01:10:50,000
They don't dare.
They love you too much and fear--

841
01:10:50,200 --> 01:10:51,720
Don't discuss my children.

842
01:10:51,920 --> 01:10:53,760
You've got to hear, you're
never home--

843
01:10:53,960 --> 01:10:55,400
I don't want to hear more!

844
01:10:55,600 --> 01:10:58,040
I know you don't, but you've got to!

845
01:10:58,800 --> 01:11:00,880
-Liesl's not a child.
-Not one word--

846
01:11:01,120 --> 01:11:03,880
Soon she'll be a woman
and you won't even know her.

847
01:11:04,120 --> 01:11:07,080
Friedrich wants to be a man
but you're not here to show--

848
01:11:07,320 --> 01:11:08,640
Don't you dare tell me--

849
01:11:08,840 --> 01:11:11,960
Brigitta could tell you about him.
She notices everything.

850
01:11:12,200 --> 01:11:15,200
Kurt acts tough to hide the pain
when you ignore him. . .

851
01:11:15,400 --> 01:11:16,880
. . .the way you do all of them.

852
01:11:17,120 --> 01:11:19,440
Louisa, I don't know about yet.

853
01:11:19,680 --> 01:11:22,760
The little ones just want love.
Please, love them all.

854
01:11:23,000 --> 01:11:24,480
I don't care to hear more.

855
01:11:24,720 --> 01:11:28,640
-I am not finished yet, captain!
-Oh, yes, you are, captain!

856
01:11:30,120 --> 01:11:31,240
Fräulein.

857
01:11:32,440 --> 01:11:36,440
Now, you will pack
your things this minute. . .

858
01:11:36,640 --> 01:11:39,040
. . .and return to the abbey.

859
01:11:41,520 --> 01:11:42,840
What's that?

860
01:11:44,480 --> 01:11:45,480
It's singing.

861
01:11:46,120 --> 01:11:48,800
Yes, I realize it's singing.
But who is singing?

862
01:11:49,720 --> 01:11:51,240
The children.

863
01:11:54,000 --> 01:11:55,280
The children?

864
01:11:55,800 --> 01:11:58,440
I taught them something to sing
for the baroness.

865
01:12:03,840 --> 01:12:09,640
My heart wants to sing
Every song it hears

866
01:12:09,880 --> 01:12:12,360
Every song that it hears

867
01:12:12,600 --> 01:12:17,840
My heart wants to beat like the wings
Of the birds that rise

868
01:12:18,080 --> 01:12:21,080
From the lake to the trees

869
01:12:21,320 --> 01:12:22,680
To the trees

870
01:12:22,920 --> 01:12:27,640
My heart wants to sigh
Like a chime that flies

871
01:12:27,840 --> 01:12:32,280
From a church on a breeze

872
01:12:32,520 --> 01:12:36,280
To laugh like a brook
When it trips and falls

873
01:12:36,520 --> 01:12:39,360
Over stones on its way

874
01:12:39,600 --> 01:12:40,960
On its way

875
01:12:41,200 --> 01:12:45,440
To sing through the night

876
01:12:45,640 --> 01:12:51,080
Like a lark who is learning to pray

877
01:12:51,320 --> 01:12:55,640
I go to the hills

878
01:12:55,840 --> 01:13:01,840
When my heart is lonely

879
01:13:02,080 --> 01:13:05,640
I know I will hear

880
01:13:05,880 --> 01:13:11,440
What I've heard before

881
01:13:12,200 --> 01:13:16,280
My heart will be blessed

882
01:13:16,520 --> 01:13:23,200
With the sound of music

883
01:13:24,040 --> 01:13:29,040
And I'll sing...

884
01:13:29,240 --> 01:13:37,040
...once more

885
01:14:08,920 --> 01:14:10,640
Edelweiss!

886
01:14:14,400 --> 01:14:17,440
You never told me how enchanting
your children are.

887
01:14:25,720 --> 01:14:27,240
Don't go away.

888
01:14:32,120 --> 01:14:33,440
Fräulein.

889
01:14:36,680 --> 01:14:37,840
I. . .

890
01:14:39,200 --> 01:14:41,920
. . .behaved badly. I apologize.

891
01:14:43,640 --> 01:14:47,040
I'm far too outspoken.
It's one of my worst faults.

892
01:14:47,440 --> 01:14:48,840
You were right.

893
01:14:51,200 --> 01:14:53,040
I don't know my children.

894
01:14:54,280 --> 01:14:58,240
There's still time, captain.
They want so much to be close to you.

895
01:14:58,520 --> 01:15:02,240
And you brought music back
into the house.

896
01:15:03,520 --> 01:15:04,920
I'd forgotten.

897
01:15:07,520 --> 01:15:08,840
Fräulein.

898
01:15:11,200 --> 01:15:12,440
I want you to stay.

899
01:15:16,280 --> 01:15:18,920
I ask you to stay.

900
01:15:20,680 --> 01:15:24,040
-If I could be of any help.
-You have already.

901
01:15:24,600 --> 01:15:25,600
More than you know.

902
01:15:44,520 --> 01:15:45,840
Marta.

903
01:15:46,480 --> 01:15:47,720
Curtain!

904
01:15:50,240 --> 01:15:53,440
High on a hill was a lonely goatherd

905
01:15:54,920 --> 01:15:58,040
Loud was the voice
Of the lonely goatherd

906
01:15:59,440 --> 01:16:02,640
Folks in a town
That was quite remote heard

907
01:16:04,120 --> 01:16:07,240
Lusty and clear
From the goatherd's throat heard

908
01:16:18,280 --> 01:16:21,040
Marta. Marta!

909
01:16:23,320 --> 01:16:25,240
Gretl, the prince!

910
01:16:26,920 --> 01:16:30,240
A prince on the bridge
Of a castle moat heard

911
01:16:31,600 --> 01:16:33,880
Men on a road
With a load to tote heard

912
01:16:36,280 --> 01:16:39,440
Men in the midst
Of a table d'hôte heard

913
01:16:40,720 --> 01:16:43,840
Men drinking beer
With the foam afloat heard

914
01:16:54,440 --> 01:16:57,440
One little girl
ln a pale pink coat heard

915
01:16:59,040 --> 01:17:02,240
She yodeled back
To the lonely goatherd

916
01:17:03,320 --> 01:17:06,640
Soon her mama
With a gleaming gloat heard

917
01:17:08,080 --> 01:17:11,240
What a duet for a girl and goatherd

918
01:17:55,920 --> 01:17:59,040
One little girl
ln a pale pink coat heard

919
01:18:00,480 --> 01:18:03,640
She yodeled back
To the lonely goatherd

920
01:18:04,920 --> 01:18:08,240
Soon her mama
With a gleaming gloat heard

921
01:18:09,600 --> 01:18:12,640
What a duet for a girl and goatherd

922
01:18:14,240 --> 01:18:15,840
Happy are they

923
01:18:18,720 --> 01:18:21,840
Soon the duet will become a trio

924
01:18:45,320 --> 01:18:46,840
-Bravo!
-Bravo!

925
01:18:47,040 --> 01:18:48,440
Very good!

926
01:18:50,200 --> 01:18:52,040
Wonderful!

927
01:18:52,600 --> 01:18:55,640
-Can we keep the puppets, Uncle Max?
-Yes, can we?

928
01:18:55,840 --> 01:18:57,800
Of course you may, my darlings.

929
01:18:58,000 --> 01:19:02,040
Why else did I tell Professor Kohner
to send the bill to your father?

930
01:19:05,600 --> 01:19:07,240
Well done, fräulein.

931
01:19:09,640 --> 01:19:11,480
I really am very much impressed.

932
01:19:11,720 --> 01:19:13,640
They're your children, captain.

933
01:19:20,520 --> 01:19:22,760
My dear, is there anything
you can't do?

934
01:19:23,000 --> 01:19:25,240
Well, I'm not sure
I'll make a good nun.

935
01:19:25,440 --> 01:19:28,440
If you have any problems,
I'd be happy to help you.

936
01:19:31,440 --> 01:19:32,800
Attention, everyone!

937
01:19:33,000 --> 01:19:36,280
I have an announcement to make.
Surprise! Surprise!

938
01:19:36,520 --> 01:19:38,760
Today, after a long
and desperate search. . .

939
01:19:39,000 --> 01:19:43,800
. . .I have found a most exciting
entry for the Salzburg Folk Festival.

940
01:19:44,000 --> 01:19:45,760
Congratulations, Max.

941
01:19:46,000 --> 01:19:48,840
And who will you
be exploiting this time?

942
01:19:50,520 --> 01:19:53,640
-The Saint lgnatius Choir?
-Guess again.

943
01:19:54,320 --> 01:19:58,080
Well, let me see now.
The Klopmann Choir?

944
01:19:58,320 --> 01:20:00,560
-No, no, no, no.
-No, no?

945
01:20:00,800 --> 01:20:01,960
Tell us.

946
01:20:02,160 --> 01:20:05,480
A singing group all in one family.
You'll never guess, Georg.

947
01:20:05,720 --> 01:20:08,480
What a charming idea!

948
01:20:08,720 --> 01:20:10,440
Whose family?

949
01:20:11,280 --> 01:20:12,840
Yours.

950
01:20:13,040 --> 01:20:15,240
They'll be the talk of the festival.

951
01:20:18,000 --> 01:20:20,880
-Well, now, what's so funny?
-You are, Max.

952
01:20:21,120 --> 01:20:24,120
You're expensive, but very funny.

953
01:20:24,840 --> 01:20:27,080
-They'll be a sensation!
-No, Max.

954
01:20:27,320 --> 01:20:29,400
It's a wonderful idea.
Fresh, original.

955
01:20:29,600 --> 01:20:34,240
Max! My children
do not sing in public.

956
01:20:34,880 --> 01:20:36,760
You can't blame me for trying.

957
01:20:36,960 --> 01:20:39,840
Children, who shall we hear
from next?

958
01:20:42,520 --> 01:20:43,640
Who?

959
01:20:49,520 --> 01:20:50,720
Yes.

960
01:20:53,480 --> 01:20:55,320
The vote is unanimous.

961
01:20:56,120 --> 01:20:57,640
You, captain.

962
01:20:57,880 --> 01:20:59,040
Me?

963
01:20:59,840 --> 01:21:02,040
-I don't understand.
-Please.

964
01:21:08,000 --> 01:21:10,040
No, no, no, no.

965
01:21:10,280 --> 01:21:12,240
I'm told that you were quite good.

966
01:21:12,440 --> 01:21:15,640
-That was a very, very long time ago.
-I remember, Father.

967
01:21:15,880 --> 01:21:18,640
-Play us something we know.
-Oh, please, Father.

968
01:21:21,400 --> 01:21:22,440
Well. . . .

969
01:21:32,280 --> 01:21:34,360
-Why didn't you tell me?
-What?

970
01:21:34,600 --> 01:21:36,840
To bring along my harmonica.

971
01:21:39,080 --> 01:21:41,120
Edelweiss

972
01:21:42,640 --> 01:21:44,840
Edelweiss

973
01:21:45,880 --> 01:21:51,840
Every morning you greet me

974
01:21:52,080 --> 01:21:55,000
Small and white

975
01:21:55,800 --> 01:21:59,040
Clean and bright

976
01:21:59,240 --> 01:22:01,960
You look happy...

977
01:22:02,160 --> 01:22:05,840
... to meet me

978
